1153:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** * \details
1154:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  This function performs single scanning of one sensor in the widget configured
1155:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  by the CapSense_CSDSetupWidgetExt() function. It does the following
1156:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  tasks:
1157:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *    1. Sets the busy flag in the CapSense_dsRam structure.
1158:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *    2. Performs the clock-phase alignment of the sense and modulator clocks.
1159:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *    3. Performs the Cmod pre-charging.
1160:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *    4. Starts single scanning.
1161:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1162:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  Calling this function directly from the application layer is not
1163:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  recommended. This function is used to implement only the user's specific
1164:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  use cases (for faster execution time or pipeline scanning for example).
1165:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  This function is called when no scanning is in progress. I.e.
1166:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  CapSense_IsBusy() returns a non-busy status.
1167:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *
1168:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  The sensor must be preconfigured by using the
1169:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  CapSense_CSDSetupWidgetExt() API prior to calling this function.
1170:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c **** *  The sensor remains ready for a next scan if a previous scan was triggered
